  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate whether cloxacillin lock is effective in
      prevention of double lumen infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Double lumen infection is one of the causes of morbidity and mortality in hemodialysis
      patients. Many strategies used to prevent it and one of them is antibiotic lock. Thus we
      select chronic hemodialysis patients and divided them into 2 groups. One group received
      cloxacillin and heparin as catheter lock and the second group received only heparin lock.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
